@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container mt-5">
    <h1 class="display-4">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <p>Welcome to the Reservation App's Privacy Policy. Your privacy is important to us, and we want you to feel comfortable using our services. Here, we outline how we collect, use, and protect your personal information.</p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We collect various types of information when you use our services, including but not limited to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Your name, email, and contact information when you make a reservation.</li>
        <li>Details about the restaurants you view and interact with on our platform.</li>
        <li>Information about your device and usage patterns to improve our services.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use the collected information to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Facilitate and personalize your reservations.</li>
        <li>Improve and optimize our platform for a better user experience.</li>
        <li>Send you relevant updates and notifications about your reservations.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Protecting Your Information</h2>
    <p>We take the security of your information seriously. We implement measures to protect against unauthorized access and use of your data.</p>

    <h2>Updates to the Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We'll notify you of any significant changes via email or through our platform.</p>

    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions or concerns about our Privacy Policy, please don't hesitate to <a href="@Url.Action("Contact", "Home")">contact us</a>.</p>
</div>
